BLOODYBUSH
EDGE

Wilfrid
Wilson
Gibson

Bloodybush
Edge
is
a
remote
spot
on
the
border-line
between
England

and
Scotland,
marked
by
a
dumpy
obelisk,
on
which
is
inscribed
an

old
scale
of
tolls.
A
rough
sandy
road
runs
down
across
the
dark

moors,
into
England
on
the
one
hand,
and
into
Scotland
on
the

other.
It
is
a
fine,
starry
night
in
early
September.
Daft
Dick,
a

fantastic
figure,
in
appearance
half-gamekeeper,
half
tramp

as

country-gentlemen)

Scottish
